OL,3,CScottish Borders Council to sell
OL,4,Cformer public toilets
OL,6,FCouncillor Simon Mountford, Executive
OL,7,FMember for Estate Management and
OL,8,FPlanning said: "As part of our
OL,9,Frationalisation of the Council's
OL,10,Festate, we have identified these
OL,11,Fpublic toilet facilities as buildings
OL,12,Fwhich could be sold on to alleviate
OL,13,Fthe pressure on our property portfolio.
OL,15,F"We recognise that these facilities
OL,16,Fare valuable resources for the local
OL,17,Fcommunities they serve and by offering
OL,18,Fthem up via the community asset
OL,19,Ftransfer method we are offering
OL,20,Fcommunities the opportunity to secure
OL,21,Fthe buildings for community use."
